  "text": "Lipids were extracted and analysed as follows from membranes, SMA solubilised membranes, or purified proteins, prepared as described above, following the procedure of Bligh and Dyer [CITATION_1] . Briefly, 200 µl of lipid-containing samples were added to 1.5 mL chloroform:methanol, 20 µl HCl 1 M and mixed over 1 hour. Phase separation was achieved by a 3 min centrifugation at 9,000×g and the lipid-containing organic phase was collected. Debris were washed by adding 500 µl chloroform, again centrifuged and the organic phases pooled. Four drops of benzene were added to the organic fraction and well mixed. Lipids were dried under nitrogen before resuspending in 200µl methanol:chloroform 2:1 (vol/vol). Lipid extracts were stored under nitrogen at -20",
